A computer program (also called software) A set of instructions that tells a computer what to do Software comes in two broad categories System software – programs that operate the computer e.g Operating Systems such as Microsoft Windows, Linux Application software – allows users to complete tasks e.g. creating documents, calculating paychecks Hardware – The physical devices that make up a computer system Internally, it is constructed from circuitry that consists of small on/off switches Machine language – most basic circuitry-level language Expressed as a series of 1s and 0s 1s represent switches that are on, and 0s represent switches that are off Not easy to write a program in machine language
